jobs.description:
Work from home! Acorn Environmental is seeking an entry- to mid-level environmental analyst in the greater Sacramento area
to join our small, collaborative team and assist with a range of environmental planning and compliance projects. This position provides an opportunity to develop expertise in a specialized consulting practice supporting Native American Tribes with environmental planning and compliance for fee-to-trust, land management, natural resources, and development projects.

About Us Acorn Environmental is a dynamic women-owned environmental planning and analysis firm specializing in services for tribal governments, public agencies, and private sector clients. We are experts in compliance with the National Environmental Policy Act (NEPA), California Environmental Quality Act (CEQA), tribal environmental policies and ordinances, natural resources, and related environmental laws and regulations. We have a reputation for delivering high quality environmental services and endeavor to grow our team of experienced professionals by investing in the development of our people. As a small business, our associates benefit from regular interaction and one-on-one guidance from highly experienced and successful environmental compliance experts. Our office is located in El Dorado Hills, California, but the majority of our staff enjoy working remotely. For additional information, please visit our website at: https://www.acorn-env.com/

A Day in the Life As a small business, our staff are constantly collaborating in real-time to meet project deadlines as a team. This is a remote position; however, candidates must be based in California, with preference for candidates located in the greater Sacramento region. Occasional travel for meetings, project coordination, or site visits is required. Typical tasks may include but are not limited to:

Researching and writing sections of larger CEQA and NEPA environmental compliance documents;
Writing reports and memorandums, including summarizing research and survey results;
Writing sections of Master Plans and other similar tribal planning documents;
Assisting in preparing marketing proposals and scopes of work;
Word processing and editorial tasks, such as line editing, document formatting, PDF compilation, and conducting acronym and reference checks;
Conducting document formatting, including formatting to support Section 508 compliance;
Preparing PowerPoint slides for presentations;
Occasional overnight travel for client meetings; and
Checking in and collaborating with colleagues.

Our business model provides the freedom to innovate and tailor your career towards the subjects that interest you most, whether it be planning, biological resources, water resources, GIS mapping, or technical editing.

Requirements Must be based in the greater Sacramento region of California;

Bachelor’s degree in environmental science/planning/policy or similar field;
Recent college graduates welcome;
Approximately one or more years of experience in planning, environmental analysis, working with Native American Tribes, or a closely related field (college schooling counts);
Excellent writing skills and grammar (Oxford comma usage a must);
Excellent communication and organizational skills (a writing sample will be requested);
High attention to detail;
Experience using Microsoft Office Suite; and
Experience writing planning documents, proposals, and/or sections of environmental compliance documents for compliance with NEPA or CEQA a plus.

Benefits We offer a full suite of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance for our staff. We offer flexible hours to accommodate work/life balance, or for staff working in various time zones or who just enjoy traveling. Other benefits include paid vacation/sick time and paid holidays. Starting compensation for this position will vary depending on the experience and educational background of the selected candidate but is anticipated to range from $55,000 to $80,000.

To Apply To be considered for this position, please send a cover letter, resume, two references, and one writing sample to careers@acorn-env.com
. Thank you!

